# Frontend MVVM Boundaries

Target-state rule: ViewModels and DataSources are not implemented yet in this
repo. The boundary convention below applies from the first ViewModel onward,
not to the current presentational-only skeleton.

React components render observable model state and forward events only.
ViewModels own page state, actions, derived values, transitions, and descriptors.
DataSources own mock access now and future SDK calls, response extraction,
pagination, cancellation, and transport-level error mapping.

Small bootstrap pages may use local mock data until the page spec is marked
`Done`. Pages marked `Done` must use a DataSource for non-trivial data access.

Use List ViewModel and Item ViewModel boundaries for non-trivial repeated
rows/cards. Prefer MobX computed getters for values read by views. Keep methods
at one abstraction level.

Every non-test component file under `src/**/ui/` must live in a same-named
folder, for example `ui/ProductCard/ProductCard.tsx`. Do not add
component-folder barrels such as `ui/ProductCard/index.ts`.
